            <p>
                <lb n="1"/><g type="ddanda"/><g type="circleMed"/><g type="ddanda"/> gavayan· bhaṭāra I ḍi<unclear>hya</unclear><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor">ṁ dyun pirak· brat·</supplied> 
<abbr><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor">k</supplied>ā</abbr> <num value="4">4</num> rambutnya lpas· <g type="ddandaHooked"/><g type="circleMed"/><g type="ddandaHooked"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
               <listApp>
                  <app loc="1">
                     <lem>ḍi<unclear>hya</unclear><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor">ṁ</supplied></lem>
<rdg source="bib:Bosch1924_01">diyaṁ</rdg>
                     <note>What remains visible on the photographs clearly shows that Bosch's reading was doubly negligent, omitting not only the diacritical mark on the <foreign>d</foreign> but also the <foreign>h</foreign> before the <foreign>y</foreign>.</note>
                  </app>
               </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" resp="part:argr">
 	<p>Produced for the Lord of Dieng. Silver vase weighing 4 <foreign>kāṭi</foreign>. Its hairs are loose.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <!-- 
Kakawin Ramayana 08.054
	i samīpaniṅ kanaka kalpataru,
	hana maṇḍapādbuta ya ratnamaya,
	pitiganya markata maṇik makiris,
	gavayan bhaṭāra ya isinya kabeh.

Cf.  Prasasti Salingsingan, Ia1-3 (PKMN p. 34):
	tatkāla saŋ paṅaruhan pu ca(2)tra mamuat gawai waran baŋ mas tuṅgal brat sāṅgappan kati. rambutnya udi. payuŋ pirak mawaṅku madanda mapuñcak mas tuṅgal brat sā(3)ṅgappan kati masnya udi tigaŋ kati
 -->
         </div>
